<br>
There is warm Honey berry pie, sweet cinammon rolls, a few omelettes made with one griffenne egg and several various meats(the rabbit meat one is her personal meal).  She sets the plates down and returns to the kitchen for the rest.  After all is served there are pancakes, and warm, freshly churned butter, and a tall tankard of refreshing Surefall sap..in addition to the previously served items.<br>
<br>
Salvia sits at the table with her omelette and listens intently to the tales of her guildmates.  She sits fascinated and remembers Drizle the young Vah Shir who sat here not long ago, she had wished to tell her story to Drizle, in hopes of helping her find meaning of the mark, but she is not here..so Salvia sits content listening and contemplating.<br>
<br>
&quot;Solarianne,&quot; she speaks turning to her well respected leader,&quot; I do not believe I have ever heard your story, would you be so kind as to grace us with it? There are many stories I have not heard yet...I would be so intrigued to hear them&quot;<br>
<br>
'To the Tears and our friends among them!&quot; comes the shout of Aseop the bard,&quot;May we never find our differences so great as to lead us to conflict!&quot;<br>
<br>
Salvia raises her glass and salutes the esteemed bard with a smile.  She then turns back to her guildies and awaits another story.<br>
<br>
/ooc I know that Solarainnes early history is only a few posts down, I just wanted to call attention to it in a small way. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/umirahze521.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mirahze521</A> at: 4/23/02 9:49:17 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/udrizle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drizle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/23/02 10:08:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=38.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The story of the mark</span><hr size=1> Drizle walks into the guildhall.  Her goal is to get to her room and cleaned up.  Her fur is matted with blood and dirt, in short she is a mess.  She softly pads through the hall, trying to go unnoticed.  As she passes the kitchen she hears much laughter and cheers dedicated to the Tears roaring.  Her chest swells with pride, she is glad to be back home.<br>
<br>
After her bath she dons her armor on once again and heads downstairs, just as a wood elf bard walks out of the kitchen.  Drizles natural shyness of strangers kicks in and she stops to let him go on ahead, his back turned towards her.  She walks slowly and quietly behind him, til she reaches the kitchen door.  She slips in as quietly as possible,and surveys the room.  Salvia, Solarianne and several others sit arouond a table eating breakfast.  The scent of Honeyberry pie wafts across the room.  <br>
<br>
Drizles stomach growls in response to the scent.  She licks her lips and approaches the table cautiosly.  She taps Salvia on the shoulder softly.  Salvia turns her green elven eyes toward the Vah Shir, &quot;Drizle! I was just thinking of you dear, please sit and have some food.  We are telling stories about the mark.  You are most welcome to sit and listen, or maybe tell your own tale.&quot;<br>
<br>
Drizle nods appreciatevly towards the fair druid and cuts herself a big slice of Honeyberry pie.  With a glass of Surefall sap in front of her and the warm pie in her mouth she feels the pain in her paw subside and turn into the warm pulse she feels around these people who share the mark as well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/btearsofveeshan25764.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ceggwin>Ceggwin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/30/02 6:23:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=38.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The story of the mark</span><hr size=1> A young, mischevious-looking halfling ambles in with a loose beltpouch in his palm.<br>
<br>
&quot;Silks!&quot;  the rogue mutters in a lilting Irish brogue.  &quot;Why must it always be silks they put in their pouches?  I could use a good platinum peice once in a while...&quot;<br>
<br>
The hobbit looks up to see his friend all laughing and cheering as a wood elf bows.  Eyeing a burgening purse filled with hard circular lumps, a telltale sign of coin, he creeps over to Aseop and slowly draws out a long, serrated blade to cut loose the pouch.<br>
<br>
Suddenly, the halfling feels a quick jerk as he is lifted into the air by a surprisingly strong High Elven paladin.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ceggwin Slyfoot!&quot; says Jalyna, slightly amused.  &quot;I should have known.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh, hello thar, ma'am!&quot;  answers a rather frightened halfling, dangling in the air.  &quot;  I was, uh... er...  just collectin' a debt from me ol' friend Aseop here, ain't that right?&quot;<br>
<br>
Jalyna sighs.  &quot;Ceggwin, it's a wonder there's still skin on your back.  You may be the greatest thief in the world, but you sure aren't a good liar.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;That obvious, eh?&quot; says Ceggwin with a grimace.  &quot;I should get back to practicing more often... ma'am, would you please let me down?&quot;<br>
<br>
